On Sat, Jul 19, 2003 at 04:24:06PM -0400, George Lyle wrote:
> make an adjustment every 15K or so.  The hassles I have had with points
> have been far less then the hassles I had with a Pertronix that decided
> to give up the ghost on the road.  

However lots of other people have had good results moving from points
to elec ignition. I am one of them.

> When electronic ignitions go out,
> there is no fixing them, you either replace them or go back to points.

Course, this is the same as when points go out. So when you have
electronic or points you should keep a spare set of points anyway.
Replacing the points back takes just a small amount of more time.

